                           </persName>
                        </persName> 
                  (whom <persName>sir <forename>Giles</forename> de <surname>Wachesham</surname>
                        </persName> gave unto 
                  him with his issue), to be free with all that belongs to him, for which he shall pay one penny yearly 
                  at the altar, on the day of Nativ. B.V.M. for the maintenance of the light, and to the grantor and 
                  his heirs three roots of ginger. 
